headline.main: From Cuba.; ARRIVAL OF THE STAR OF THE WEST AND THE MATANZAS THE HEALTH OF HAVANA THE MARKETS.

docs.lead_paragraph: The United States Mail steamship Star of the West, Capt. McGOWAN, left New-Orleans on the 20th at 8 A.M., arrived at Havana on the afternoon of the 22d at 7 P.M., and left the following day at 1 o'clock P.M., arriving at this port yesterday in the afternoon.

headline.main: THE NORTH PACIFIC.; What our Legislature Did, and What Narrow Escapes we have had at its Hands--Principal Appropriations--J.D. Whitney, State Geologist--A Good Governor Well Treated--A Famous Newspaper Suit Ended--The Dead Alive, d' Aumadle About Again--A French Cook's Vengeance--No More Through baggage Messengers--Mining Intelligence, Northern News, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: At the moment that my last started from the Plaza on its overland route the Legislature was adjourning. "Laus Deo," shouted the people, when they learned that the mischief-making power had actually gone into an eight months retirement, and in San Francisco many flags were run up as a token of the common joy.

docs.snippet: THE STORM The rain storm on Saturday caused considerable damage in this city. The water ran with great volume down the steep grade of Hicks into Fulton-street, doing much damage to the sewer being constructed on the former street.

docs.snippet: Last Monday morning rose tolerably brilliantly, considering the awful time of cutting east winds and snow and hail-storms we had recently experienced, and by ten o'clock Pall Mall was well filled with scattered groups, wending their way to the...
docs.lead_paragraph: Last Monday morning rose tolerably brilliantly, considering the awful time of cutting east winds and snow and hail-storms we had recently experienced, and by ten o'clock Pall Mall was well filled with scattered groups, wending their way to the exhibition of the Royal Academy. It was the opening day; the Queen had been in the previous Thursday.

headline.main: THE BAPTIST ANNIVERSARIES.; THE AMERICAN PUBLICATION SOCIETY--THE MISSIONARY UNION. FIRST DAY. SECOND DAY. THIRD DAY. NOTICES OF RELIGIOUS MOVEMENTS.

docs.lead_paragraph: A goodly number of Baptists from East, West and North have assembled here this week to receive reports from the societies under their control, and to arrange the programme for another year. First in order was the sermon before the American Baptist Publication Society, by Rev. REUBEN JEFFREY, of Philadelphia, at the Ninth-street Baptist Church, on Sunday evening last.
